<recipe>
    <name>Pad Thai Noodles - Traditional Style</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Soak rice noodles in cold water for at least 1 hour (noodles can be soaked longer and even over night). Drain and set aside. In a bowl, combine tamarind juice, fish sauce, rice vinegar, sugar, and paprika. Set aside. Heat oil in a wok, add garlic. Saut√© for 30 seconds until garlic is fragrant. Add shrimp, tofu and egg. Stir-fry for 1 minute, until egg is scrambled. Add rice noodles and tamarind juice mixture. Stir-fry all ingredients until well cooked and combined. Serve with bean sprouts on the side, peanuts sprinkled over the top, with fresh cilantro and lime wedge garnishes.

Optional garnishes: sprigs of fresh cilantro and lime wedges.</instructions>
